BLUETONGUE - EUROPE (08): FRANCE, BOVINE, SEROTYPE 8, OIE, ASSESSMENT
*********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 8 Apr 2016
Source: Le JDC [in French, trans. Corr.SB, edited]
http://www.lejdc.fr/nievre/actualite/pays/morvan/2016/04/08/quinze-cas-de-fievre-catarrhale-ovine-dans-la-nievre_11863125.html


The outbreak of bluetongue continued to spread, and is now extending to 78 departments, including 4 in Yonne, 15 in Nièvre and 6 in Saône-et-Loire with 237 outbreaks reported in total since September 2016, said the Ministry of Agriculture, on Friday (8 Apr 2016).

To date, this is a total of 237 outbreaks of bluetongue that have been detected in the center of France, including 85 in the Puy-de-Dôme, 45 in the Allier, 15 in the Nièvre, 13 in the Loire, 12 in the Creuse, 7 in the Cher and Cantal, 6 in Saône-et-Loire, Indre 5, Aveyron and Haute-Loire, 4 in Burgundy and the Rhone, 3 in Dordogne and Haute-Vienne, 2 in Lozere in Charente-Maritime in Corrèze, and 1 case in Loiret, in Isère, in the Lot, in Gironde, in Ariege and Haute-Savoie, in Doubs, in Haute-Saone and Haute-Marne, reported in an updated statement on the Ministry website.

The virus affects 78 departments and a large area covering much of France, whose epicenter is located in the Puy-de-Dôme and Allier. The so-called regulated area, where livestock movements are limited, has also been expanded and now includes all departments south of a line from the Loire-Atlantique in the southern half of the Ardennes, encompassing the island of France.

The restricted area is made up of a protection zone of 100 km [about 62 mile] radius around the affected farm, it is surrounded by a 50 km [about 31 mile]-wide surveillance zone. Within the restricted area, infected flocks are surrounded by a perimeter of prohibition 20 km [about 12 mile] radius.

In the Nièvre, the 1st case of bluetongue was detected in cattle in Anthien in October 2015.

